<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-21-0888 </DOCNO><TEXT>Rockburst mechanism can be characterized by the criteria of strength,energy and bursting liability. Strength criterion deals with the failureof coal and rock, and the other two criteria deal with the abrupt failureof coal and rock. The sufficient and necessary conditions for the occurrenceof rockburst should be that all the three criteria are fulfilled simultaneously.The so-defined mechanism can be used to describe a variety of phenomenaconcerning rockbursts. 2 refs., 4 figs., 1 tab.</TEXT></DOC>